data.enText: a person who did a job before sb else
The new president reversed many of the policies of his predecessor.
data.chText: 新任总统彻底改变了其前任的许多政策。

data.enText: a thing, such as a machine, that has been followed or replaced by sth else
data.chText: 原先的东西；被替代的事物

tr: something that precedes and indicates the approach of something or someone
one who precedes you in time (as in holding a position or office)

example.ex: He maintained that he learned everything he knew from his predecessor Kenneth Sisam.
example.tran: 他坚称他所知道的一切都获自前任肯尼思·赛瑟姆。

value.def: Your predecessor is the person who had your job before you.

example.ex: The car is some 40mm shorter than its predecessor.
example.tran: 这辆轿车比原先的车型短了约40毫米。

value.def: The predecessor of an object or machine is the object or machine that came before it in a sequence or process of development.
